questions.explanation:
Data attributes provide a standardized way to embed custom data within HTML elements without using non-standard attributes. They are semantically valid and can be accessed via JavaScript's dataset property, making them ideal for storing element-specific information. Developers can easily read and write these attributes without conflicting with standard HTML properties.

```javascript
// Accessing data attribute
let element = document.querySelector('#myElement');
let customValue = element.dataset.myCustomAttribute;

// Setting data attribute
element.dataset.newAttribute = 'value';
```
